    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-25T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-25T21:00:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.003 Wallace, Henry A./63a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-25T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 25, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>720. Department recently sent you texts of statements by President and Vice
                        President<note n="33" xml:id="d214fn33">Telegram No. 703, May 23, to the
                        Ambassador in China, <ref target="#pg_228">p. 228</ref>.</note> concerning
                    latter’s visit to China. Following are arrival dates principal points on
                    journey: Washington to Edmonton May 20, Fairbanks 21st (Cross date line lose one
                    day), Anadyr 23rd, Yakutsk 31st, Irkutsk June 5, Semipalatinsk 15th, Tashkent
                    17th, Alma Ata 20th, Tihwa 22nd, Chungking 23rd, Kunming 26th, Kweilin 28th,
                    Chengtu 30th, Sian, Tungkuan and Lanchow July 2, Ulan Bator 3rd, Chita 5th.
                    Arrive in United States 9th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
